_text = "I moved to Alberta about 3 years ago. People often asked me why I left Kelowna for Lethbridge. I think its a silly question to determine ones beauty in comparison to another.\n\nSouthern Alberta may not have the mountains immediately there, but there is so much beauty in other forms.\n\nMy first summer here, I was often outdoors, documenting whatever I could find. What always stood out to me was the vast fields of grain. The way the wind moved the stalks made me think of the ocean, and the waves.\n\nI think there's something really beautiful in that."
